{{arabic name|Al Nahyan}} {{use dmy dates|date=February 2016}} {{Infobox royalty | name = Sultan bin Khalifa Al Nahyan | title = Sheikh | image = | caption = | spouse = | issue = | full name = | styles = | succession = | reign = | reign-type = | predecessor = | successor = | father = [[Khalifa bin Zayed Al Nahyan]] | mother = [[Shamsa bint Suhail Al Mazrouei]] | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1965}} | birth_place = [[Al Ain]] | death_date = | death_place = | burial_date= | burial_place= | house = [[Al Nahyan family]] | religion = [[Islam]] }}
'''Sultan bin Khalifa Al Nahyan''' (born 1965) is a [[Emirati people|Emirati]] royal military officer, businessman and member of [[Abu Dhabi]]'s ruling family, [[Al Nahyan family|the Al Nahyans]].
==Early life and education== Sultan was born in [[Al Ain]] in 1965.<ref name=equefed/> He is the son of [[Khalifa bin Zayed Al Nahyan|Khalifa bin Zayed]], ruler of Abu Dhabi and the president of [[the United Arab Emirates|the United Arab Emirates (UAE)]].<ref name=maz14may/>
He holds a bachelor's degree in political and administrative sciences, which he received from [[Emirates University]].<ref name=equefed/> He also graduated from Zayed bin Sultan Military College in Al Ain in March 1988. Then he attended [[Royal Military Academy Sandhurst|the Sandhurst Royal Military Academy]] and graduated in 1989.<ref name=equefed/> He received a master's degree in political science from [[the University of Salford]] in July 1989.<ref name=equefed/> Additionally, he holds two PhDs: one in international studies from [[University of Limerick|the University of Limerick]] in November 1998 and the other from [[Nasser Military Academy|Nasser Higher Military Academy]] in [[the Arab Republic of Egypt]] in April 1999.<ref name=equefed/>
==Career== Sultan was promoted to the rank of [[lieutenant colonel]] staff pilot in 1999 and then to the rank of colonel staff in February, 2000.<ref name=equefed/> He is the advisor to the president of the UAE, Khalifa bin Zayed, and the board chairman of the SBK Holding.<ref>{{cite web|title=Chairman's message|url=http://www.sbkholding.com/ChairmanMessage.html|work=SBK Holding|accessdate=17 April 2013}}</ref> In addition, he is a member of the UAE's equestrian federation.<ref name=equefed>{{cite web|title=Board members|url=http://www.uaeequafed.ae/bodpres.htm|work=Emirates Equestrian Federation|accessdate=17 April 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120405142810/http://www.uaeequafed.ae/bodpres.htm|archivedate=5 April 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He is among the board members of [[Executive Council of Abu Dhabi|the Executive Council of Abu Dhabi]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Khalifa restructures Abu Dhabi Investment Authority's board|url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Khalifa+restructures+Abu+Dhabi+Investment+Authority's+board.-a0325419741|accessdate=20 April 2013|newspaper=Khaleej Times|date=9 April 2013}}</ref>
===Business activities=== His firm provides mediation between businesspeople, for instance, between [[Roman Abramovich]] and [[Boris Berezovsky (businessman)|Boris Berezovsky]] in 2001.<ref name=maz14may>{{cite news|author=Yelena Mazneva|title=Sheiks aids Abramovich, Berezovsky|url=http://sptimes.ru/index.php?action_id=2&story_id=31441|accessdate=17 April 2013|newspaper=St. Petersburg Times|date=14 May 2010|location=Moscow}}</ref>
