{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2015}} {{Use British English|date=February 2015}} Since 2001, the '''''[[Sunday Times]]''''' newspaper has published annual '''lists of the best companies to work for''' in the [[United Kingdom|UK]]. The award is highly valued by its winners.<ref>For example, [https://www.theguardian.com/money/2005/jun/25/workandcareers.jobsandmoney Don't call me boss], ''[[The Guardian]]'', 25 June 2005</ref>
The list ranks Britain's best companies to work for based a number of criteria. It is mainly based on [[questionnaire|surveys]] of [[Job satisfaction|staff satisfaction]].<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/2996224.stm How to get a stress-free workplace], [[BBC News]], 17 June 2003</ref>
