'''Vientirauha Oy''' (literally ‘Peace of Export Joint-Stock Company’, meaning ‘Freedom of Export Ltd’) was a [[paramilitary]] [[strikebreaking]] organization established in Finland in 1920, with 34&nbsp;000 members at its peak.
